  "text": "Lastly, in a long-term 52-week study, aripiprazole and lithium were analyzed head-to-head in a double-blind manner. In the stabilization phase, Bipolar I disorder subjects with initial manic or mixed episodes were treated double-blind with the above-mentioned medications for 12 weeks. Those who achieved sustained remission (YMRS and MADRS scores ≤ 12), were followed in the same manner for a further period of 40 weeks. Statistics were drawn on observed cases only, and although there was a high attrition rate, the completers of the study had equivalent benefit in the prevention of manic and mixed episodes. In contrast to lithium, data showed that aripiprazole was better tolerated with fewer and less severe adverse events [CITATION_1] . ",
